external_knowledge:
- "Quintet" refers to a group of five;
- "Left their mark on the field" refers to players with significant game participation and notable achievements;
- "Touchdown prowess" refers to the number of touchdowns scored by a player;
- "Interception challenges" refers to the number of interceptions thrown by a player;
- "Illuminate the total score their teams have accumulated" refers to the total score of the team across all games in which the player participated.

- "shine the brightest" refers to having the highest average score difference;
- "playing away games" refers to games where the team is not playing at their home venue;
- "outshine their opponents" refers to the team's score being higher than the opponent's score on average.

- 'Regular season' refers to the main part of the sports league's schedule, excluding playoffs and pre-season games;
- 'Home games' are games played at the team's own stadium;
- 'Touchdown' is a scoring play in American football, worth six points;
- 'Attendance' refers to the number of spectators present at the game.
